                  BEFORE the Right Hon. WILLIAM CUBITT, M.P. Lord Mayor of the City of London; the 


                     Right Hon. Sir George Bramwell, Knt., one of the Barons of Her Majesty's Court of Exchequer; the Hon. Sir John Barnard Byles, one of the Justices of Her Majesty's Court of Common Pleas; John Humphrey, Esq.; Thomas Challis, Esq.; and Thomas Quested Finnis, Esq.; Aldermen of the said City; Russell Gurney, Esq. Q.C. Recorder of the said City; 


                     William Ander
son Rose, Esq.; Thomas Gabriel, Esq.; and Edward Conder, Esq.; Aldermen of the said City; 


                     Thomas Chambers, Esq. Common Serjeant of the said City; and Robert Malcolm Kerr, Esq. Judge of the Sheriff's Court of the said City; Her Majesty's Justices of Oyer and Terminer and General Gaol Delivery of Newgate, holden for the said City, and Judges of the Central Criminal Court.
